### 11.1. Test Points

| Ref | Net | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| TP101 | +3V3 | |
| TP102 | +3V3_M.2 | Not implemented (M.2) |
| TP103 | +5V | |
| TP104 | +VBAT_BUS | |
| TP105 | GND | |
| TP106 | PMUX1_ST | 5V mux status |
| TP107 | PMUX2_ST | Not implemented (3V3 mux) |
| TP108 | I2C_4_SCL | Not implemented (3V3 PoL) |
| TP109 | I2C_4_SDA | Not implemented (3V3 PoL) |
| TP110 | SPI_2_CS | Payload bus SPI |
| TP111 | SPI_2_PICO | Payload bus SPI |
| TP112 | SPI_2_POCI | Payload bus SPI |
| TP113 | SPI_2_SCL | Payload bus SPI |
| TP114 | UART_1_TX | Payload bus UART |
| TP115 | UART_1_RX | Payload bus UART |
| TP116 | UART_1_RTS | Payload bus UART |
| TP117 | UART_1_CTS | Payload bus UART |
| TP118 | GPIO2_BUS | Spare payload GPIO (CM5 GPIO25) |

### 11.2. Indicators

See [Indicator LEDs](#107-indicator-leds).

### 11.3. Buttons

Both buttons are CK KMS223GP LFG.

- **SW101 (PWR_BUT)**: Push briefly to power the CM5 on or off. Hold for more than 5 seconds to force the CM5 to shut down.
- **SW102 (RESET)**: Push to turn the PMIC off, for resetting the board without a full power cycle.

### 11.4. Configuration Jumpers

All configuration jumpers are short-pad type, normally open, and pull the relevant line to GND when closed.

| Ref | Signal | Function when closed |
|---|---|---|
| J102 | BOOT | Force RPIBOOT (USB device mode, for firmware install) |
| J103 | WL-EN | Disable WiFi (regulatory compliance) |
| J104 | BT-EN | Disable Bluetooth (regulatory compliance) |
| J105 | USBOTG_ID | Set USB host mode (correct OS driver must be used) |
| J106 | EEPROM_WP | Enable EEPROM hardware write protection |

## 12. Known Limitations & Design Decisions

- **M.2 not implemented**: The M.2 Key-M connector (J501) and its 3.3V PoL chain (U304, U303, U501) are present in the schematic but were not placed on the board, because usable component height on the bottom copper is limited to 1.49 mm. As a result the board carries a single power mux and a single PoL module.
- **Bus 3.3V / 5V rails unused**: The board runs from VBAT only. The 3.3V and 5V bus rails are broken out to unpopulated headers (J107, J108) but are otherwise unused.
- **No inhibit logic**: There is no RBF / deployment-switch inhibit on this board.
- **No watchdog**: No external watchdog is fitted.
- **I2C3 is shared**: The on-board gyro (0x68) and 5V PoL (0x08) share I2C3 with the payload bus. Ensure no address conflicts with external devices added on the bus.
- **No external I2C pull-ups**: All three I2C buses rely on the CM5's internal 1.8 kΩ pull-ups. External devices on the payload bus must not assume board-side pull-ups beyond this.
- **Gyro only**: The IAM-20380 is a 3-axis gyroscope with no accelerometer or magnetometer; it provides angular rate only.
- **Not flight-qualified**: This board is for development and bring-up. It has not been qualified for space flight.

## 13. Revision History

| Version | Date | Summary |
|---|---|---|
| v1r1 | 2026-06-13 | Initial sample build. CM5 carrier respun from CM5_MINIMA_REV2. Single 5V PoL (FS1603A-5000) and single power mux (TPS2121). On-board IAM-20380 gyro and CY15B102Q FRAM. M.2 and 3.3V PoL chain laid out in the schematic but not implemented on the board. |

## 14. Notes

Designed for development and bring-up. Not flight-qualified.

